  "body": "The [message] object stores and outputs any kind of message in Pd. As an object, $1/$2 loads arguments when used in an abstraction, so the syntax is not the same as a message box. Nonetheless, it deals with comma and semicolons in the same way as regular message boxes do. See [pd syntax] for more details."
